[
  {
    "text": "♪ Mellow instrumental hip-hop music ♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪ ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=3"
  },
  {
    "text": "Hi, folks. My name is Pavlo. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "I work on security technologies ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=11"
  },
  {
    "text": "that help keep you and your users safe. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=12"
  },
  {
    "text": "Today I'm going to tell you about some upcoming changes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=15"
  },
  {
    "text": "that may impact the way you develop, test, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=17"
  },
  {
    "text": "and deploy your applications. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, I want to tell you what Developer Mode is, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=22"
  },
  {
    "text": "the reasoning behind why it was created, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=25"
  },
  {
    "text": "the security benefit it brings, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=27"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the workflows that it will affect. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=29"
  },
  {
    "text": "Then, we will discuss when and how ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "to turn on Developer Mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=34"
  },
  {
    "text": "And then we will finish off this session with a walk-through ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=37"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the tools we built to support automation flows ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=40"
  },
  {
    "text": "for when you're working with many devices, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=42"
  },
  {
    "text": "like in a testing lab environment. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=44"
  },
  {
    "text": "OK, so what is Developer Mode? ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=47"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's a new mode in iOS 16 and watchOS 9 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "that enables common developer workflows. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=52"
  },
  {
    "text": "Developer Mode is disabled by default ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=55"
  },
  {
    "text": "and requires you to explicitly enroll the device ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=58"
  },
  {
    "text": "into Developer Mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=60"
  },
  {
    "text": "Your enrollment persists across reboots and system updates. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=61"
  },
  {
    "text": "And of course, we have built tools ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=65"
  },
  {
    "text": "that enable you to automate Developer Mode setup ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=67"
  },
  {
    "text": "if you want. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=69"
  },
  {
    "text": "A natural question you will have is, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=71"
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Why are we introducing Developer Mode?\" ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=72"
  },
  {
    "text": "The reason is that powerful developer features ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=75"
  },
  {
    "text": "are being abused in targeted attacks. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "Meanwhile, the vast majority of users ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=80"
  },
  {
    "text": "do not need such functionality ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "and so they shouldn't be enabled by default. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=83"
  },
  {
    "text": "This way we can retain the development capabilities ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=86"
  },
  {
    "text": "that you rely on and increase the security for users ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=88"
  },
  {
    "text": "with mitigations that otherwise would get in your way. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=91"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now having said that, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "most common distribution flows will not require Developer Mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=96"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, deploying your application through TestFlight ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=99"
  },
  {
    "text": "or using Enterprise in-house distribution ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=101"
  },
  {
    "text": "does not require Developer Mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=103"
  },
  {
    "text": "And of course, distributing your applications ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=106"
  },
  {
    "text": "through the App Store does not require Developer Mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=108"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's only required for when you, the developer, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=112"
  },
  {
    "text": "are actively developing your application on your device. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=114"
  },
  {
    "text": "All right, by this point I'm sure you can't wait ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=117"
  },
  {
    "text": "until I tell you how you would get started ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=119"
  },
  {
    "text": "with using Developer Mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "So let's go through when you need to turn on Developer Mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=123"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how to do it. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=125"
  },
  {
    "text": "You should turn Developer Mode on if you need to ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=127"
  },
  {
    "text": "run and install development signed applications, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=130"
  },
  {
    "text": "including applications signed by using a Personal Team; ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=132"
  },
  {
    "text": "debug and instrument your applications; ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=136"
  },
  {
    "text": "or you want to use testing automation on your device. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=138"
  },
  {
    "text": "Turning on Developer Mode is straightforward, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=143"
  },
  {
    "text": "but first you need to connect your device to Xcode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=144"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the Developer Mode menu item to appear. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=147"
  },
  {
    "text": "The beta releases that you have downloaded ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=150"
  },
  {
    "text": "will have the menu item always visible for the time being. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=152"
  },
  {
    "text": "Installing a development-signed application without Xcode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=156"
  },
  {
    "text": "like through Apple Configurator, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "will also make the menu item visible. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=160"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once you've done that, you can find the Developer Mode controls ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=163"
  },
  {
    "text": "under Privacy & Security in Settings. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=165"
  },
  {
    "text": "And for automation, you can use the new devmodectl ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=169"
  },
  {
    "text": "that ships by default on macOS Ventura, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=172"
  },
  {
    "text": "but more on that later. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=174"
  },
  {
    "text": "OK, so let's walk through ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=176"
  },
  {
    "text": "with how you would turn on Developer Mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=178"
  },
  {
    "text": "In front of me, I have an iPhone 13 Pro ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=180"
  },
  {
    "text": "that I just picked up to run my code on. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=182"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, I'm going to plug it in to my Mac ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=183"
  },
  {
    "text": "that has Xcode already running. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=185"
  },
  {
    "text": "As you can see, Xcode recognizes that this device ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=188"
  },
  {
    "text": "does not have Developer Mode enabled ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=191"
  },
  {
    "text": "and will prevent me from running this application. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=193"
  },
  {
    "text": "But now that I have plugged it in, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=197"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can go into Settings, Privacy & Security, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=199"
  },
  {
    "text": "Developer Mode.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "Turning on Developer Mode requires that you reboot your device, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=210"
  },
  {
    "text": "so let's go ahead and do that.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=212"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once the device has rebooted, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=217"
  },
  {
    "text": "you will be prompted once again to confirm your decision. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=218"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once you tap Turn On, you will be good to go. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=222"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, Xcode sees that the device has Developer Mode enabled, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=226"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I can run my application.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=232"
  },
  {
    "text": "While this flow works when you're working ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=239"
  },
  {
    "text": "with a single device, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=240"
  },
  {
    "text": "this process can be time consuming ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=241"
  },
  {
    "text": "if you're dealing with multiple devices. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=243"
  },
  {
    "text": "For this reason, we've built tools ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=245"
  },
  {
    "text": "that help you automate this process. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=246"
  },
  {
    "text": "Automation flows have one limitation: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=249"
  },
  {
    "text": "only devices without a passcode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=251"
  },
  {
    "text": "can have Developer Mode automatically enabled. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=252"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is because when you restart your iPhone ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=255"
  },
  {
    "text": "you need to unlock your device ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=257"
  },
  {
    "text": "before your device can be interacted with. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=258"
  },
  {
    "text": "To support automation, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=261"
  },
  {
    "text": "macOS Ventura ships with devmodectl ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=263"
  },
  {
    "text": "that you can use to either enable Developer Mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=265"
  },
  {
    "text": "on a single device that you have already connected, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=267"
  },
  {
    "text": "or in Streaming Mode that will automatically turn on ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=269"
  },
  {
    "text": "Developer Mode on all devices that you plug in.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=271"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here I have two devices plugged into my Mac.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=276"
  },
  {
    "text": "They don't have passcodes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=283"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I don't want to manually set up Developer Mode on them. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=284"
  },
  {
    "text": "So I'm going to run devmodectl with the streaming subcommand. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=286"
  },
  {
    "text": "This will automatically reboot the connected devices ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=290"
  },
  {
    "text": "and set up Developer Mode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=293"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once Developer Mode has been set up, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=296"
  },
  {
    "text": "you will get a notification on the device.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=298"
  },
  {
    "text": "And now these devices are good to go. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=305"
  },
  {
    "text": "All right, that's all I have for you today. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=308"
  },
  {
    "text": "To wrap it up, in iOS 16 and watchOS 9 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=310"
  },
  {
    "text": "you will have to enable Developer Mode ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=313"
  },
  {
    "text": "to perform common development activities ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=314"
  },
  {
    "text": "like deploying and debugging your applications. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=316"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if you need to automate Developer Mode setup, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=319"
  },
  {
    "text": "you can use devmodectl, which ships in macOS Ventura. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=321"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you want to learn more about security changes ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=325"
  },
  {
    "text": "that may impact your macOS distribution workflows, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=327"
  },
  {
    "text": "check out the \"What's new in notarization for Mac apps\" talk. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=329"
  },
  {
    "text": "I hope you have a great rest of your day ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=333"
  },
  {
    "text": "and happy coding! ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=334"
  },
  {
    "text": "♪",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2022-110344/?time=335"
  }
]